      "side": 1,
      "message": "while L172 loop runs, we might get way beyond MaxBatchSizeApprox. We should be checking each time we increment batchSize. It is the same problem as before: we might be buffering the entire artifact.\n\nI think this callback @L163 is doing more than it should. In particular, creation of rowC channel for each artifact looks suspicious. \n\nalso, eg.Wait() is never called.\n\nI recommend:\n- in queryTextArtifacts, accept rowC as a parameter. Call downloadArtifactContent like it does already, except there is no need for error group in this queryTextArtifacts. This means that chunks of different artifacts would go to the same channel\n- move the batching logic to exportTextArtifactsToBigQuery. Reuse eg that already exists there. Iterate over rowC, produce batches, check batchSize each time it is incremented.",
